HEADWORD: Laryngismus
<hw>Lar`yn*gis"mus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>laryggismo`s</grk> a croaking. See <er>Larynx</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A spasmodic state of the glottis, giving rise to
contraction or closure of the opening.</def>⟦br⟧
